  "prompt": "What are some of the best Soft Rock songs of all time?",
  "response": "Soft rock, known for its melodic tunes and smooth vocals, has produced many timeless classics. Here are some of the best soft rock songs of all time:\n\n1. **\"Hotel California\" by Eagles** - This iconic track features intricate guitar work and haunting lyrics.\n\n2. **\"Your Song\" by Elton John** - A beautiful, heartfelt ballad that showcases Elton John's piano skills and tender vocals.\n\n3. **\"Landslide\" by Fleetwood Mac** - A reflective and emotional song sung by Stevie Nicks, considered one of the band's masterpieces.\n\n4. **\"Fire and Rain\" by James Taylor** - A poignant song that combines introspective lyrics with gentle acoustic guitar.\n\n5. **\"Don't Stop Believin'\" by Journey** - Known for its uplifting melody and powerful vocal performance from Steve Perry.\n\n6. **\"Rich Girl\" by Hall & Oates** - A catchy tune with a memorable chorus, reflecting the duo's characteristic sound.\n\n7. **\"Sailing\" by Christopher Cross** - A smooth, soothing track that evokes a sense of calm and relaxation.\n\n8. **\"I Will Always Love You\" by Whitney Houston** - While often considered a pop or ballad, its soft rock influences are undeniable.\n\n9. **\"Wild World\" by Cat Stevens** - A classic track with thoughtful lyrics and a gentle melody.\n\n10. **\"More Than a Feeling\" by Boston** - Known for its soaring vocals and lush harmonies.\n\nThese songs have all had a significant impact on the genre, showcasing the best of soft rock's ability to blend rock influences with softer, more melodic elements.",
